Jordan’s 2-Month Trade Deficit Widens on Oil, Machinery Imports

-- B y   M a s s o u d   A .   D e r h a l l y
-- 
2011-04-16T11:45:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/jordan-s-2-month-trade-deficit-widens-on-oil-machinery-imports.html
Jordan’s trade deficit widened 19.6
percent in the first two months of the year as oil, iron,
plastics and machinery imports increased, the  Department of
Statistics  said.  The shortfall increased to 1 billion dinars ($1.4 billion)
through February from 843.7 million dinars in the same period a
year ago, the department said today in an e-mailed statement.  Crude oil imports rose 20 percent, plastics increased 34.7
percent, iron jumped 70 percent and machinery surged 59 percent,
the department said.  Total imports advanced 20 percent. Exports gained about 22
percent in the first two months as potash rose 84.7 percent,
phosphate advanced 47.6 percent and vegetables climbed 23.8
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Massoud A. Derhally in Beirut, Lebanon at 
